text: Dami Im ( , , ; born October 17, 1988) is a South Korean-born Australian singer. She represented Australia at the Eurovision Song Contest in 2016, coming second with "Sound of Silence". She won the fifth season of The X Factor in 2013. Her first album was an ARIA number one. She has three studio albums, two extended plays, nine singles, two album appearances, and four music videos. Im was born in Incheon. Her family moved to Australia when she was 9. She grew up in Brisbane, Queensland. She is married and lives in Daisy Hill, a suburb of Logan City, Queensland.
